<!--
  FIXTURE. Synthetic HL7 v3 SPL. The DRUG AND ALL CONTENT ARE INVENTED and describe no real
  product; only the STRUCTURE is real.

  This fixture reproduces the nesting of a real innovator oncology label (verified live against
  DailyMed setid 046a9011-3911-4d3f-a15f-fbb56d5aad56, TEMODAR, spl_version 40, on 2026-07-13).
  The defect it pins:

    * WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS (43685-7) carries NO direct <text>. Every warning lives in a
      <component><section> subsection coded 42229-5 (SPL UNCLASSIFIED SECTION). A parser that
      reads only a coded section's direct <text> collects ZERO warnings and says so silently —
      a drug with six labeled warnings presents as having none.
    * ADVERSE REACTIONS (34084-4) carries a short direct preamble and puts the substance in
      subsections 90374-0 (Clinical Trials Experience) and 90375-7 (Postmarketing Experience).
    * <excerpt> holds the SPL "Highlights" RESTATEMENT of the same warnings. It must NOT be
      collected: it would double-count every finding.

  Also pinned here: absence-of-evidence (no boxed warning, no drug-interactions section — a
  genuinely absent section must stay 0 and never be invented) and deterministic de-duplication
  (5.6 repeats 5.1's sentence verbatim, as real labels do).
-->
